00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:26,041
Brains. Brains.
What wrong with my brains?

3
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:28,875
If I don't pass
this test, I'm screwed.

4
00:02:28,958 --> 00:02:31,208
If you don't watch your
grades, you're gonna end up

5
00:02:31,291 --> 00:02:33,333
in summer school with
the rest of the dummies.

6
00:02:33,416 --> 00:02:35,708
I may not be the smartest
zombie, but I know that

7
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:37,208
the only thing
worse than having to

8
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,416
drag my ass to school everyday
in the heat of the summer

9
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,791
is frying up like a piece
of bacon on the way there.

10
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:44,750
Quit daydreaming! Now a
spiral galaxy spins around

11
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:47,583
and around, exactly
like a top. Picture it.

12
00:02:47,666 --> 00:02:49,916
That top spinning around
just like this, but to get

13
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,208
this thing going you're
gonna need a humongous string!

14
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:56,125
That's the whole idea
behind "string theory".

15
00:02:56,208 --> 00:02:58,625
Wait. Oh yeah.
Since we're on the subject,

16
00:02:58,708 --> 00:03:01,000
lemme tell you some more
about universal string theory.

17
00:03:01,083 --> 00:03:03,708
A long time ago,
in a galaxy far, far away

18
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:05,791
this lesson
stopped being useful.

19
00:03:05,875 --> 00:03:08,416
I just asked for
some help on a math problem.

20
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:10,458
Haruna, you know
what this one is?

21
00:03:10,541 --> 00:03:12,208
Root of three minus root of two.

22
00:03:12,291 --> 00:03:14,625
So genius. How'd you find that?

23
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:16,041
What?

24
00:03:16,125 --> 00:03:18,875
The answer. Why does this
equal what you just said?

25
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:20,416
What's one plus one?

26
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,333
It's two.

27
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:22,833
And why is that?

28
00:03:22,916 --> 00:03:25,750
Because it just is. That's why.

29
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,166
That's right!

30
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:29,458
Okay. But I have
to show all the steps

31
00:03:29,541 --> 00:03:31,750
I take to get
there on this test.

32
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:34,000
I can't just say
"it is because it is."

33
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:38,250
It won't be easy,
but get ready to learn!

34
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:39,708
And for some reason

35
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:41,791
to get to the solution
of this math problem,

36
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:44,458
we have to start back at
the beginning of the universe.

37
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:47,041
It's a long journey
and way more boring

38
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:49,333
than I could
have ever dreamed.

39
00:03:49,416 --> 00:03:53,208
Hey! Don't fall asleep on me!

40
00:03:54,166 --> 00:03:56,958
See these. Besides just
being cute, I put these animals

41
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:59,791
on the board for a reason.
Although it's very complicated

42
00:03:59,875 --> 00:04:02,583
and will probably take the
rest of the night to explain,

43
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:04,500
so I hope you're ready.

44
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:10,750
You look like you could use a
hand, if you know what I mean!

45
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:14,208
Oh, you have absolutely no idea
how happy that would make me.

46
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:20,708
Whoa! Awesome! The whole
thing's completely done already!

47
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,916
Let me do it, so you'll
be able to understand.

48
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,500
Eu already wrote
everything down for me, so...

49
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:29,291
Yeah, but this is gonna
make a whole lot more sense.

50
00:04:34,125 --> 00:04:35,791
So, you get it now, or what?

51
00:04:35,875 --> 00:04:38,541
Oh yeah. Clear as gravy.

52
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:42,375
Geez. You're so stupid.
Take a look at this one here.

53
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:44,458
It moves like a snake
and chases the bunny rabbit

54
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:45,250
in the rocket...

55
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,750
Yep, I am totally screwed.

56
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:59,250
I don't know how it happened,
but I think Haruna somehow

57
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:01,583
taught me something about math.

58
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:04,625
Maybe there's a reason
she calls herself a genius.

59
