so I brought you here.

202
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:14,958
You got some
kinda problem with that?

203
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:17,583
Uh. No, 'course not.

204
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:29,833
So good!

205
00:13:29,916 --> 00:13:31,375
Ain't it, though?

206
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:34,625
I would've never thought a bowl
of ramen could be this good!

207
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:37,375
I love your pork!

208
00:13:39,708 --> 00:13:40,708
Take it.

209
00:13:40,791 --> 00:13:43,416
Thanks. Not big on pork?

210
00:13:43,791 --> 00:13:45,125
Pork rules.

211
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:46,916
So why did you give it to me?

212
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,666
Just shut up and
put it in your mouth, okay?

213
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:52,416
Okay. But if you
love it so much.

214
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:55,083
Listen, just eat it, will ya?

215
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:59,833
You bet. But, hey,
it's your loss. Thanks!

216
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:03,333
Mmm-mmmmm!
This is so freakin' good!

217
00:14:03,416 --> 00:14:05,416
It's like a party in my mouth.

218
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:09,291
Okay.

219
00:14:11,458 --> 00:14:13,791
There's like, a ton
more if you want it.

220
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:15,583
Oh you don't mind? That's cool.

221
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:19,416
Well in that case.
Go ahead and pork me! Uh...

222
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,083
Isn't the whole reason
we came here so you could

223
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:23,666
explain how you used this
stuff to beat those megalos?

224
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:27,208
Yeah, I forgot.
Wanna know? It's so cool.

225
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:29,916
We tried every single ramen
cart, stand and restaurant

226
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,708
we could find.
We ate bowl after bowl

227
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:33,666
and developed a
complex rating system.

228
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:36,375
We would mark the shops with
stars. Three being the highest.

229
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:38,541
We then went back to all the
three star places,

230
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:40,833
stole the recipes, and then
through countless hours

231
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:44,583
of experimentation came
up with the ultimate recipe!

232
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:47,000
That doesn't really
explain anything.

233
00:14:47,083 --> 00:14:49,000
What I wanna know is how come
when you threw it on those

234
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:52,541
megalos, it made them
disappear? Why does that work?

235
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,791
You sure are curious.
It's a long story,

236
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:57,125
but I'll have to
start at the beginning.

237
00:14:57,208 --> 00:15:00,375
Is it? Great.
Another long story.

238
00:15:02,875 --> 00:15:07,166
Ya get it now?
Cause if not. Don't ask me.

239
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:10,291
I ain't gotta clue about how
any of this stuff really works.

240
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:12,875
Yeah. That's pretty
obvious to me now.

241
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:14,375
I don't know nothin'
about noodle theory

242
00:15:14,458 --> 00:15:16,708
or any of that kinda crap,
either. But if ya want,

243
00:15:16,791 --> 00:15:18,916
I might could find someone
around here that does.

244
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,291
No, it's cool.

245
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:21,875
Oh yeah!
Don't worry about a swarm

246
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:24,500
of megalos invading the town,
'cause we got this bad boy here

247
00:15:24,583 --> 00:15:26,583
